name: Arkona
Comment: Construction started in August 2016. First turbine brought online in September 2018. Inaugurated in April 2019.

name: Bard Offshore-1
Comment: First phase of 240 MW completed in August 2013. Acquired by Macquarie Infrastructure in August 2019.

name: Borkum Riffgat
Comment: The wind farm is finished since July 2013 but it remains grid connection work.

name: Borkum Riffgrund-1
Operator: Borkum Riffgrund I Offshore Windpark A/S GmbH & Co. oHG

name: Borkum Riffgrund-2
Comment: Orsted divested 50% of the project to Global Infrastructure Partners (GIP) in December 2017. All turbines produce power as of November 2018 and commercial operations are expected shortly. The commissioning of the project is expected for early December 2018.

name: Gode Wind 2
Comment: Total cost of Gode Wind 1 & 2 projects of DKK16.4bn (2013).

name: Meerwind SüdIOst
Comment: Construction started in August 2012 and was completed in April 2014. In June 2016, Blackstone sold its 80% in the plant to China Three Gorges.

name: Nordergrunde
Comment: John Laing acquired a 30% stake from wpd in August 2016.

name: Veja Mate
Comment: Connected to the German grid in December 2016 and first power in January 2017.

name: Hohe See
Comment: In November 2012, EnbW decide to delay its investment decision to an undetermined date. FID in late 2016. In February 2017, Enbridge acquired a 49.9% stake in the project. Foundation works started in February 2019. July 2019 : first production fed into the grid.

name: Deutsche Bucht - GB
Comment: Highland Group sold 100% of the project to Northland Power in March 2017. July 2019 : First power delivered, full power expected for the end of 2019.
